import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', hue='source', data=data, palette='bright')
    plt.title('What is the trend in net electricity generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    plt.legend(title='Source', loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation')
    ax = sns.barplot(data=data, ci=None)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of net electricity generation across different energy sources?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    ax.legend(title='Energy Source', loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    sns.color_palette("pastel")
    sns.set_palette("pastel")
    sns.set(font_scale=1.2)
    sns.set_style("ticks", {"xtick.major.size": 8, "ytick.major.size": 8})
    plt.title("Proportion of net electricity generation for each energy source", wrap=True)
    plt.pie(data['net_generation'], labels=data['source'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, counterclock=False)
    plt.legend(title="Energy Source", loc="center left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data) # data already contains the data to be plotted. Always include this line. DO NOT modify the rest of the code template.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="source", y="net_generation", data=data, palette="Set3")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of net electricity generation for each energy source?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Energy Source")
    plt.ylabel("Net Electricity Generation (MWh)")
    plt.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['net_generation'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data) # data already contains the data to be plotted. Always include this line. DO NOT modify the rest of the code template.
